# Progress Diagram

Maintain a living mermaid diagram in `docs/reports/PROGRESS.md` that visualizes the current implementation progress.

## Rules

- After completing any todo or implementation step, update the diagram in `docs/reports/PROGRESS.md`.
- Each node in the diagram represents a major task (project setup, schemas, nodes, frontend, etc.).
- Node labels must include the task name and its status.
- Use subgraphs to group related steps (Backend, Frontend, Docs, etc.).
- Keep a "Current Step" marker pointing to what is being worked on right now.

## Status Markers

Use these prefixes in node labels to indicate status:

- Completed: `"[done] Task Name"`
- In Progress: `"[NOW] Task Name"`
- Pending: `"[ ] Task Name"`

## Example

The diagram should follow this pattern:

````markdown
# Implementation Progress

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    subgraph Backend ["Backend Agent"]
        A["[done] Project Setup"]
        B["[done] Settings & Config"]
        C["[NOW] Taxonomy"]
        D["[ ] Schemas"]
        E["[ ] Prompts"]
        F["[ ] Supabase Service"]
        G["[ ] Preprocessor Node"]
        H["[ ] Vision Node"]
        I["[ ] Tagger Nodes"]
        J["[ ] Validator + Filter + Aggregator"]
        K["[ ] Graph Builder"]
        L["[ ] Entry Point"]
        A --> B --> C --> D --> E --> F --> G --> H --> I --> J --> K --> L
    end

    subgraph API ["API Layer"]
        M["[ ] FastAPI Server"]
        N["[ ] Docker"]
        L --> M --> N
    end

    subgraph Frontend ["Next.js Dashboard"]
        O["[ ] Project Setup"]
        P["[ ] Components"]
        Q["[ ] Integration"]
        M --> O --> P --> Q
    end

    subgraph Documentation ["Docs"]
        R["[ ] Quickstart"]
        S["[ ] Architecture"]
        T["[ ] Reports"]
        R --> S --> T
    end
```

**Last updated:** YYYY-MM-DD
**Currently working on:** Task name
````
